==English==

===Etymology===
Originally in plural, from Old French ''[[brachez]]'', plural of ''[[brachet]]'', a diminutive of Provençal ''[[brac]]'', from Old Frankish.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/bræʧ/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ætʃ|-ætʃ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# {{archaic}} a [[hound]], especially female
#*'''1605''': Mastiff, greyhound, mongrel grim, / Hound or spaniel, '''brach''' or him — William Shakespeare, ''King Lear III.vi''

